transcripts.text: They didn't reach a decision on it.  But the question you've just been asking raises a point I wanted to say when Senator Hirono was talking, which is how did we get to the point here where the evidence is now that the president was falsely accused of colluding with the Russians and accused of being treasonous and accused of being a Russian agent.  And the evidence now is that was without a basis.  And two years of his administration have been dominated by the allegations that have now been proven false.  And, you know, to listen to some of the rhetoric, you would think that the Mueller report had found the opposite.
